                        "__typename": "EmployerReviewRG",
                        "advice": "Please hear teachers out when they have concerns, instead of shoving them under a carpet.  Also check in on how your employees are doing, pretend to atleast care. The job gets too stressful. Appreciate your employees, maybe the teacher retention rate will improve.",
                        "adviceOriginal": null,
                        "cons": "*Long hours (10hrs on sat and sun). Winter and summer academy are worse. \r\n*It drained my soul, no work life balance.\r\n*They care more about money than the actual kids and education. \r\n*Racist towards black people(some staff and parents). They had a problem that I'm from South Africa and pronounce things differently(eg. Zed instead of Zee). Had a few kids pulled out of my class due to my race and nationality \r\n*Management is horrible. They don't care how you feel, your opinion doesn't count and they lack ability to solve problems. When you voice out concerns, they ask  the teacher what they'll do about it. Somethings are beyond teachers control and require management to solve them.\r\n*Pay isn't enough-There are honestly other places that pay better.\r\n*Staff retention is really low.",
                        "consOriginal": null,
