                        "cons": "I worked in a summer camp in England as Teaching Leader, which I thought it would have been cool for the salary and for my CV, but you realize as soon as you start that even though salary is good compared to other companies, you are basically working the whole day and everything is so disorganized that makes the experience even more stressful. Kids are paying a crazy amount of money for something improvised, but they'll obviously have fun anyway because they're kids and mostly because you are there for them so you don't care if yoi sleep 4 hours and you've been working nonstop, you just give them all of your energy, and they need a lot. You have 1 day off in which they say that you could go on a trip but you'd probably  be so dead inside that you'll spend it laying on the bed in silence. I also had a lot of fun with coworkers, but we were all so stressed and tired that was crazy.",
