                    {
                        "__typename": "EmployerReviewRG",
                        "advice": "-",
                        "adviceOriginal": null,
                        "cons": "- Feedback policy - You have to keep an average rating made by students\r\n- Group classes can be challenging if the students are not on the same level \r\n(example: They all want to practice speaking but the time is limited (40 minutes, 6 people in the class). More advanced students want to talk more, the less advanced students also want to talk more but they speak too slowly. Therefore the more advanced are impatient, less advanced feel rushed. You may get negative feedback as&nbsp;\"I prefer if the teacher corrects me more\" or \"Please give me more opportunities to participate\" or \"I prefer a more patient teaching style\" etc.&nbsp;This can lower your score. And it's not your fault. However after a while you learn more how to navigate them more efficiently. I still prefer private classes.",
